ntrager-tire-levers-best-297x101.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05162604/bontrager-tire-levers-best-800x272.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05162604/bontrager-tire-levers-best-120x41.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05162604/bontrager-tire-levers-best-768x261.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05162604/bontrager-tire-levers-best-1536x522.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05162604/bontrager-tire-levers-best-696x237.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05162604/bontrager-tire-levers-best-1068x363.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05162604/bontrager-tire-levers-best-1235x420.jpg 1235w\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=0d15472d-796a-41f7-afb4-32437118891b&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.trekbikes.com%2Fus%2Fen_US%2Fequipment%2Fbike-accessories%2Fbike-tools-maintenance%2Fbontrager-tire-lever-set%2Fp%2F07799%2F\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bontrager’s tire levers</a> don’t look like anything fancy, but Bikerumor editors tend to gravitate to them for nearly every ride. They’re designed with angled side tips that can finesse their way under the tightest of tires, with rounded edges that are unlikely to damage anything…even rim tape.</p><p>They’re also designed to fit comfortably in your hand and are slightly longer than most tire levers in order to provide more leverage. They’re also a bit thicker than others, so they’re great for big hands. We also love that they snap together so that one never goes missing in the depths of your saddlebag.</p><p>They only come in one color at the moment—red—so if you prefer a simple black set or want a wilder colorway, you’ll want to look elsewhere. But if you’re all business and just want a simple set of tire levers that will do the job, Bontrager has your back.</p><ul><li>Color: Red</li><li>Dimensions: 34 grams</li><li>Price: $5</li></ul><h3><span>&nbsp;<strong>BEST AT HOME TIRE LEVERS</strong>: <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08NX28H4M/?tag=20br-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Clever Standard Clever Lever</a></span><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever.jpg\" alt=\"clever tire lever\" width=\"1600\" height=\"885\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-297x164.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-800x443.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-120x66.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-768x425.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-1536x850.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-696x385.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-1068x591.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-759x420.jpg 759w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-297x164.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-800x443.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-120x66.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-768x425.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-1536x850.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-696x385.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-1068x591.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155650/clever-tire-lever-759x420.jpg 759w\"></a></h3><p>Want a tire lever that does more than just pry off tight tires? Enter the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/06/02/new-clever-standard-flatout-tire-lever-fixes-your-chain/\">Clever Standard Clever Lever</a>, a weirdly fancy set of tire levers that seems gimmicky on the surface but is actually super useful.</p><p>One Bikerumor editor keeps them perched on his workstand for breaking open quick links as well as removing tight tires. The two tire levers interlock together to form a set of quick link pliers to make removing or reassembling a master chain link easy. It can also tighten or remove valve cores. And the levers themselves are designed to be non-slip so if your hands are slick with sweat, you’ll still be able to use them easily.</p><p>These levers might be a bit overbuilt, especially if you have a chain breaker on your multitool. But if you love a cool gadget, they’re great.</p><ul><li>Color: Black</li><li>Dimensions: 130mm length, 60 grams</li><li>Price: $14</li></ul><h3><span>&nbsp;<strong>BEST NON-TUBELESS TIRE LEVERS</strong>: <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F843163%2Fcrankbrothers-speedier-tire-lever\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Crank Brothers Speedier Tire Lever</a>&nbsp;</span></h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1600\" height=\"686\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-297x127.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-800x343.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-120x51.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-768x329.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-1536x659.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-696x298.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-1068x458.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-980x420.jpg 980w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-297x127.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-800x343.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-120x51.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-768x329.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-1536x659.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-696x298.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-1068x458.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/05155434/Crank-Brothers-Speedier-Tire-Lever-980x420.jpg 980w\"></a></p><p>For when we don’t want to bash our hands trying to unseat the most stubbornly tight tires, Crank Brothers’ Speedier Tire Lever&nbsp;is our go-to. And yes, the “Lever” rather than “LeverS” is purposeful: You only get one.</p><p>Rather than your usual set of two, this lever comes solo, but boasts a protected handhold that protects your fingers should it slip out just as you’re giving it your all. If you know what we’re talking about, then you’ll appreciate just how ingenious this is for preventing you from punching your spokes at full speed. Think, plastic knuckles…not bloody knuckles..</p><p>The reverse side has a hook that slides over the rim to help you reseat tight tires, too. With modern tubeless tires being much easier to mount and dismount, we’d say this is best for those still running tube-type road tires, or newbies just learning to change their own tires and tubes. Like all Crank Brothers products, the <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=e295c418-295a-447c-b265-734e25f82503&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F843163%2Fcrankbrothers-speedier-tire-lever\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Speedier Lever</a> comes with a lifetime guarantee.</p><ul><li>Color: Black</li><li>Dimensions: 144mm length, 26 grams</li><li>Price: $6</li></ul><h3><span><strong>&nbsp;MOST ERGONOMIC TIRE LEVERS</strong>:<a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00IWRX01E/?tag=20br-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> Unior Tire Levers</a>&nbsp;</span></